com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.platform.server.tcp

Class TcpReverseProxyServer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.platform.server.tcp.TcpServer
      • com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.platform.server.tcp.TcpReverseProxyServer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Server

    @ThreadSafe
public final class TcpReverseProxyServer
extends TcpServer
    A reverse TCP proxy. This proxy simply transfers data (requests) from clients (front-ends) to servers (back-ends) and transfers data back (responses) from back-ends to front-ends, thus hiding back-ends from front-ends and front-ends from back-ends.

      • TcpReverseProxyServer

        @Inject
public TcpReverseProxyServer(@TcpReverseProxyServerFrontEndAddress
                                     InetSocketAddress feAddress,
                                     @TcpReverseProxyServerBackEndAddress
                                     InetSocketAddress beAddress,
                                     @TcpReverseProxyServerName
                                     String name,
                                     @TcpReverseProxyServerBoss
                                     Integer maxBossThreads,
                                     @TcpReverseProxyServerWorker
                                     Integer maxWorkerThreads,
                                     @TcpReverseProxyServerThreadFactory
                                     ThreadFactory threadFactory,
                                     @TcpReverseProxyServerConnectTimeout
                                     Integer connectTimeoutMillis)
        Constructs a new instance of TcpReverseProxyServer.
        Parameters:
        feAddress - InetSocketAddress the TcpReverseProxyServer will listen to (front-end address).
        beAddress - InetSocketAddress the TcpReverseProxyServer will forward requests to (back-end address).
        name - A name of the TcpReverseProxyServer.
        maxBossThreads - Maximum number of Threads that accept new TCP connections.
        maxWorkerThreads - Maximum number of Threads that process data received via the accepted TCP connections.
        threadFactory - A ThreadFactory that will be used to create boss and worker Threads. Thread names MAY not be the same as the threadFactory generates.
        connectTimeoutMillis - Amount of time in milliseconds to wait for connecting to the beAddress. This argument MUST be positive.
